member.name: M:Unigine.Engine.setBackgroundUpdate(bool)
member.summary: Sets the value indicating whether the application window is updated when the window is hidden or out of focus (rendering frames in background). By default your UNIGINE application stops rendering frames and updating its main window, when it window goes out of focus (e.g. user switches to another window). Setting the background update mode enables constant rendering regardless of whether the Engine window is focused or in the background.
member.param: Engine window update mode: true for constantly repeating update cycle (i.e. the application is updated even if the window is hidden or out of focus); otherwise, false.

member.name: M:Unigine.Engine.isBackgroundUpdate
member.summary: Returns a value indicating whether the Engine window is updated when the window is hidden or out of focus.
member.returns: true if the update cycle is constantly repeated (i.e. the application is updated even if the window is hidden or out of focus); otherwise, false.

member.name: M:Unigine.Engine.addWorldLogic(WorldLogic)
member.summary: Adds a WorldLogic instance to the engine runtime. Instances of the WorldLogic class should not be added while the world is loaded and the world script is being executed (as you can't change a world script while the world is loaded). In such a case the init() method shall not be called if the WorldLogic is added before opening the world.
member.returns: true if the WorldLogic instance has been added successfully; otherwise, false.

member.name: M:Unigine.Engine.startFps
member.summary: Starts the FPS counter if it was stopped. All function calls are placed into a stack, so the number of calls to this function should correspond to the number of calls to the stopFps() function.

member.name: M:Unigine.Engine.stopFps
member.summary: Stops the FPS counter. This function should be called if application window is hidden or some heavy non-rendering tasks are processing. All function calls are placed into a stack, so the number of calls to this function should correspond to the number of calls to the startFps() function.

member.name: M:Unigine.Engine.addCallback(Unigine.Engine.CALLBACK_INDEX,Unigine.CallbackBase)
member.summary: Adds a callback for the specified stage of the execution sequence. Callback functions can be used to get access to WorldLogic::update(), node update, GUI (and callback) update, WorldLogic::postUpdate() within the main loop.
member.param: Stage of the execution sequence for which a callback is to be added. One of the CALLBACK_* variables.The _BEGIN prefix corresponds to the beginning of the execution sequence step, _END to its completion.
member.returns: ID of the last added callback of the specified type, if the callback was added successfully; otherwise, nullptr. This ID can be used to remove this callback when necessary.

member.name: M:Unigine.Engine.removeCallback(Unigine.Engine.CALLBACK_INDEX,void)
member.summary: Removes the specified callback from the list of callbacks for the specified stage of the execution sequence. Callback functions can be used to get access to WorldLogic::update(), node update, GUI (and callback) update, WorldLogic::postUpdate() within the main loop.
member.param: Stage of the execution sequence for which a callback is to be added. One of the CALLBACK_* variables.The _BEGIN prefix corresponds to the beginning of the execution sequence step, _END to its completion.
Callback ID obtained when the callback is added.
member.returns: True if the callback with the given ID was removed successfully; otherwise false.

member.name: M:Unigine.Engine.clearCallbacks(Unigine.Engine.CALLBACK_INDEX)
member.summary: Clears all added callbacks for the specified stage of the execution sequence. Callback functions can be used to get access to WorldLogic::update(), node update, GUI (and callback) update, WorldLogic::postUpdate() within the main loop.
member.param: Stage of the execution sequence for which a callback is to be added. One of the CALLBACK_* variables.The _BEGIN prefix corresponds to the beginning of the execution sequence step, _END to its completion.

member.name: F:Unigine.Engine.GCMODE_DEFAULT
member.summary: Default C# garbage collector mode. In this case heavy spikes and excessive memory consumption are imminent if you don't manage your objects properly and do not use the Dispose() method.

member.name: F:Unigine.Engine.GCMODE_USE_MEMORY_PRESSURE
member.summary: Passes the information about C++ memory consumption to C#. This results in more frequent GC calls preventing the application from eating too much memory right after startup and removing heavy spikes.

member.name: F:Unigine.Engine.GCMODE_EVERY_FRAME
member.summary: The garbage collector is called every frame. This results in overall performance reduction, but removes heavy spikes.

member.name: F:Unigine.Engine.GCMODE_WORLD_SHUTDOWN
member.summary: The garbage collector is called on closing the world. This mode is ideal if the number of memory allocations is your code is insignificant.
